583	| Space | To                                | From                              | Notes                     |
584	| ----- | --------------------------------- | --------------------------------- | ------------------------- |
585	| HSL   | (native storage)                  | `ColorValue::new(h, s, l, a)`     | Canonical internal format |
586	| RGB   | `to_rgb() -> (u8, u8, u8)`        | `from_rgb(r, g, b) -> Self`       | 0-255 per channel         |
587	| HEX   | `to_hex(include_alpha) -> String` | `from_hex(hex) -> Option<Self>`   | `#rrggbb` or `#rrggbbaa`  |
588	| HSB   | `to_hsb() -> (f64, f64, f64)`     | via `with_channel(Brightness, v)` | Hue shared with HSL       |
589	| CSS   | `to_css_hsl() -> String`          | --                                | `hsl()`/`hsla()` string   |
590	
591	Color space conversion rules:
592	
593	1. Out-of-gamut values are clamped to the target color space's valid range during conversion (e.g., HSL saturation > 100% clamped to 100%).
594	2. Channel values are rounded to the precision appropriate for the color space: RGB channels to integers (0-255), HSL/HSB hue to 1 decimal place, saturation/lightness to integers.
595	3. When switching color spaces in the UI, the displayed value is the conversion result of the current color -- no rounding trip-loss accumulation (convert from stored high-precision internal representation each time).
